# Create Quality Spec (Project Overlay)

The full skill — risk tiers, behavior-to-test-layer mapping, security coverage, explicit out-of-scope, and an observable definition of done — is in the `praxis` plugin's `create-quality-spec` skill. Read it first.

## Project-specific paths

- Lives at: `{{paths.waves}}/wave-NNN-<slug>/qa.md`
- Test layers and runners: `.github/skills/write-tests/SKILL.md` (the project's Pyramid Test Strategy specifics)
- Acceptance-criteria source: the wave's `product-design.md` thin-slices

## Project-specific gates

- Led by the product designer (`.github/agents/{{personas.aliases.product_designer}}.agent.md`), paired with the principal engineer (`.github/agents/{{personas.aliases.principal_engineer}}.agent.md`) on technical risk and coverage; designer-owned when user-facing risk dominates.
- No code in `qa.md` — it specifies *what* is tested and at which layer, never the test implementation.
- Every risk-tiered behavior maps to a test layer per `.github/skills/write-tests/SKILL.md`. A high-risk seam requires a property/contract test, not a single example.

## Definition of done

The quality spec is complete when every acceptance criterion has a named test layer and an observable done-signal, and the out-of-scope list is explicit.
